cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:

1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper proposes a new path selection technique for Tor that aims to improve both performance and anonymity. It also evaluates the anonymity of the proposed technique using a new metric called CLASI.

2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on improving the performance of the Tor anonymity system by selecting efficient circuits. It also evaluates the proposed technique using live Tor experiments and Shadow simulations.

3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a Random Forest classifier as the core of the new path selection technique. The classifier is trained on recent measurements of Tor to predict the performance of a proposed path.

4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a machine learning technique (Random Forest) to predict the performance of Tor circuits. It also evaluates the performance of the proposed technique using live Tor experiments and Shadow simulations.

5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a new system (PredicTor) that improves the performance of the Tor anonymity system. It also evaluates the proposed system using live Tor experiments and Shadow simulations.
